snippet: Michael Phelps won the 200-meter individual medley for his 20th over all medal. Tyler Clary, who long has competed in the shadows of his fellow Americans, upset Ryan Lochte in the 200-meter backstroke.
abstract: Michael Phelps wins the men's 200-meter individual medley at the 2012 Olympics for his 20th career medal and his 16th gold, becoming the first man to win a swimming event at three consecutive Games; teammate Ryan Lochte takes the silver; Lochte also finishes second in the 200-meter backstroke, beaten to the wall by American teammate Tyler Clary.
lead_paragraph: Michael Phelps won the 200-meter individual medley for his 20th over all medal. Tyler Clary, who long has competed in the shadows of his fellow Americans, upset Ryan Lochte in the 200-meter backstroke.

headline.seo: Phelps Wins Gold No. 16, as Lochte Falls Short Twice
headline.main: 16th Gold for Phelps as Lochte Falls Short
